# Frontend environment overrides (development and production).
#
# Copy this file to `.env.local` if you need any of the overrides below.
# `.env.local` is gitignored — never commit real values.
#
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# NEXT_PUBLIC_API_BASE_URL
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# By default, next.config.js rewrites /api/* to http://localhost:8000 in dev.
# This works fine for short backend calls but routes through Next.js's
# internal proxy (http-proxy-middleware), which has a default timeout.
#
# As of Phase 4b, the narrative endpoint runs OpenAI calls CONCURRENTLY,
# so top-N=20 completes in ~5 seconds — well under any proxy timeout.
# You should not need to set this variable.
#
# If you ever do hit a proxy timeout (e.g. extremely slow OpenAI response,
# very large top_n on a slow connection), set this to the backend URL.
# The frontend will then call the backend directly, bypassing Next.js's
# proxy entirely. CORS is already configured in backend/api.py to allow
# requests from localhost:3000.
#
# Dev override:
#   NEXT_PUBLIC_API_BASE_URL=http://localhost:8000
#
# Production:
#   NEXT_PUBLIC_API_BASE_URL=https://your-backend-host.example.com
